# Why Textual

Textual as a framework provides terminal hacks that make creating a retro game surprisingly simple.
With just about 200 lines of code, you can create a fully playable retro game.
If you'd like to explore the code, or even play around with it, check out the script [here](./invader.py).
This script does not pretend to be production-ready invader game, just a fun toy example how to build a game with Textual.

# Game Plays

